org.influxdata.platform.option

Class WriteOptions

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.influxdata.platform.option.WriteOptions

  • @ThreadSafe
public final class WriteOptions
extends Object
    WriteOptions are used to configure writes the data point into InfluxDB.

    The default setting use the batching configured to (consistent with Telegraf):

    • batchSize = 1000
    • flushInterval = 1000 ms
    • retryInterval = 1000 ms
    • jitterInterval = 0
    • bufferLimit = 10_000

    The default backpressure strategy is BackpressureOverflowStrategy.DROP_OLDEST.

    For disabling the batching use the configuration: DISABLED_BATCHING

    Author:
    Jakub Bednar (bednar@github) (21/09/2018 10:11)
